minib3d + cerberus (ex-monkey)

v0.42.1 - updated for Cerberus, removed Flash, XNA targets
v0.42 - bug fixes: texture fixes, collision fixes, mobile glcontext fixes
v0.41 - bug fixes: FreeEntity(), Flash11 updates
v0.40 - android opts, collision opts 
v0.39 - multi-shaders & bug fixes
v0.38 - preloader changes
v0.37 - unified EffectState all targets
v0.36.2 - alpha testing, bug fixes
v0.35.1 - spot bug fixes, including collision bug fixes
v0.35 - mojo emulation, camera scissor
v0.34 - B3D loader fixes
v0.33 - MMD/PC2 file load, TPixmap read/write, collisions, bug fixes
v0.32 - programmable bones, Draw(x,y) for screen, loads of bugs and stability fixes
v0.31 - update to work with monkey v66, bug fixes.
v0.30 - new targets, Html5, XNA, opengl2.0, GPU shaders
v0.20 - new render encapsulation allows new render targets (opengles2.0, WebGL, etc.)

v0.14 - TTexture, animated textures, texture fixes
v0.13 - TPick, TCollisions accuracy and speed increase
v0.12 - fixed Gluproject, alpha sorting; fixed OBJ loader, B3D Loader; Base64 Android; LoadMesh fixes
v0.11 - fixes: faster TPick; ClearWorld(); TText added centering align; OBJ loader for multiple coordinates;
        Base64 Loader fix for ARM data alignment (works on iPhone, iPad)
v0.10 - first release

